{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489676","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489676"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:25:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:25:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"717"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"717","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/717"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.28,0.05,0.41,0.11,0.16]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"717"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67904"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"717","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/717"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"717"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53369"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"251"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"1536"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"3817"},{"type":"tags","id":"3890"},{"type":"tags","id":"9267"},{"type":"tags","id":"9341"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9891"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11576"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35682"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46099"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67904","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67904"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old woman with a two month history of dyspepsia and weight loss is being worked up for treatment of an endoscopically proven adenocarcinoma of the distal stomach (Image). A CT scan does not show any evidence of metastatic spread. The patient is otherwise in good health and has no significant medical history. She does not smoke, drinks two glasses of wine at weekends and is not on any medications. The physical examination is unremarkable. A further assessment is required to determine if management of the tumour can be approached with curative intent.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following investigations is most likely to help determine treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Endoscopic ultrasound","Ca-125","PET scan","MRI scan","Laparoscopy"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECarcinoma of the stomach often spreads transcoelomically. Such intra-abdominal spread and coating of the peritoneum with metastatic seedlings is relatively common. The standard investigation for staging of many gastrointestinal cancers is the CT scan, but small tumour deposits on the peritoneal surfaces can easily be missed. If such tumour deposits occur, any treatment will be palliative, rather than potentially curative.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe biological marker, Ca-125 is not a standard initial staging investigation. It has more value in the ongoing surveillance of patients treated for gastric cancer, where an elevation in the marker could suggest peritoneal disease. Endoscopic ultrasound is useful in the assessment of early gastric cancers, where the technique can be used to determine the depth of invasion of the primary tumour and the presence of any adjacent lymph nodes. The photograph of this tumour shows a deep ulcer, which indicates that it is extending beyond the submucosal layers and cannot be classified as an early gastric cancer. Endoscopic ultrasound will not help in its staging and the assessment of any possible peritoneal involvement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst PET scanning is used more frequently in the staging of oesophageal and cardia cancers, the sensitivity of this investigation with gastric cancers is variable. In this case, a PET scan is definitely not indicated and moreover, is not funded by Medicare for gastric cancer (unless at the cardia). MRI scanning is used increasingly in the staging of gastric cancer, where it can be more sensitive than CT in the detection of peritoneal metastatic disease. A more reliable staging tool when looking for evidence of peritoneal disease is \u003Cstrong\u003Elaparoscopy.\u003C/strong\u003E This investigation is performed in patients with gastric cancer if all the other investigations have suggested that the disease is localised and could be treated with curative intent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is important to appreciate that these cases will be managed through a multidisciplinary team (MDT) approach and decisions made with regards to investigations and treatment have input from specialists in gastroenterology, radiology, surgery, radiotherapy and oncology.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diagnostic laparoscopy is a key staging tool for patients with potentially curable gastric cancer."],"references":["Van Cutsem E, Sagaert X, Topal B, et al. Gastric cancer. Lancet 2016; 388:2654-64. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27156933/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53369"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"717"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16353"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16353","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16353"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/04cb40b0-d58f-4c96-a405-7f5b687fdd68.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/04cb40b0-d58f-4c96-a405-7f5b687fdd68.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":400,"height":400}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53369","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/